docs.title: GraphQL API Reference
docs.description: Welcome to the Riverr GraphQL API API reference.

docs.title: include
docs.description: Directs the executor to include this field or fragment only when the if argument is true.

docs.title: skip
docs.description: Directs the executor to skip this field or fragment when the if argument is true.

docs.title: createProduct
docs.description: Create a new product with images and variants.

docs.title: deleteProduct
docs.description: Delete a product by its ID. Returns true if successful.

docs.title: deleteShop
docs.description: Delete a shop by its ID. Returns true if successful.

docs.title: updateOrder
docs.description: Update an existing order (e.g. mark as shipped or cancelled).

docs.title: getAllShops
docs.description: Retrieve all shops associated with the current enterprise.

docs.title: getBlankProducts
docs.description: Retrieve a list of available blank products (variants/details).

docs.title: getOrder
docs.description: Retrieve a single order by its ID.

docs.title: getOrders
docs.description: Retrieve a list of orders, optionally filtered by shop, status, or date range.

docs.title: getProduct
docs.description: Retrieve a single product by its ID.

docs.title: getProducts
docs.description: Retrieve a list of products, optionally filtered by shop.

docs.title: getShipment
docs.description: Retrieve shipment details for a specific order.

docs.title: getShipments
docs.description: Retrieve a list of shipments, filtered by various criteria.

docs.title: getShop
docs.description: Retrieve a single shop by its ID.

docs.title: deprecated
docs.description: Marks an element of a GraphQL schema as no longer supported.

docs.title: oneOf
docs.description: Indicates exactly one field must be supplied and this field must not be null.

docs.title: specifiedBy
docs.description: Exposes a URL that specifies the behavior of this scalar.

docs.title: Boolean
docs.description: The Boolean scalar type represents true or false.

docs.title: Float
docs.description: The Float scalar type represents signed double-precision fractional values as specified by IEEE 754.

docs.title: ID
docs.description: The ID scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as "4") or integer (such as 4) input value will be accepted as an ID.

docs.title: Int
docs.description: The Int scalar type represents non-fractional signed whole numeric values. Int can represent values between -(2^31) and 2^31 - 1.

docs.title: String
docs.description: The String scalar type represents textual data, represented as UTF-8 character sequences. The String type is most often used by GraphQL to represent free-form human-readable text.
